<node id="China">
  <data key="d0">China</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">China is a significant market and participant in global trade, contributing to the net revenue of various companies, including a 30% share in 2025. It is a major location for the expansion of display manufacturing facilities and a substantial portion of customers and suppliers are based there. China plays a crucial role in the supply chain due to its export of certain technologies, materials, and rare earth minerals, which were subject to export controls in 2025. The country faces restrictions on exporting certain products, impacting companies like NVIDIA and their operations, due to United States government export regulations. China is also a geopolitical entity that may contribute to heightened risks of cybersecurity attacks due to ongoing tensions and conflicts. Companies must ensure compliance with export controls when shipping products to China.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f0b30e55c2d2c942c8ef27807467b3d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7481c513c84b894dbf5566a03c9c31d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85c73190292489fe36964fdd5fc32b0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d99a02cc7061af948a4068d7dfaf580&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf53d552d1955a280cebbd6e2d050c2d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b0f36135b3b08cac0302bf342d7918d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8ee469fd420dd945b64b580faff532</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
