  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">U.S. GAAP stands for accounting principles generally accepted in the United States, which the company follows for financial statement preparation.&lt;SEP&gt;U.S. GAAP refers to Generally Accepted Accounting Principles in the United States, which guide the preparation of financial statements.&lt;SEP&gt;U.S. GAAP stands for Generally Accepted Accounting Principles in the United States, which are the accounting standards used for the preparation of financial statements.</data>
