<node id="Form 10-K">
  <data key="d0">Form 10-K</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Form 10-K is an annual report filed by publicly traded companies with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). It provides a comprehensive summary of a company's financial performance, including significant accounting policies, financial statements, and outstanding shares for a fiscal year. The report contains detailed information on the company's financial performance, including income taxes, as well as notes to the consolidated financial statements. Form 10-K serves as a crucial document for investors and stakeholders to understand a company's financial health and make informed decisions. It is required by the SEC for all publicly traded companies to ensure transparency and accountability in the financial reporting process.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fe1fafd9b0c6f09af84ad373757a9b00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a36df99dfa3a16bd8e4d429df7cf42a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26fa1d1070f941c3c83605779a2af8f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-737963f5a4aa4c7ac5ff75bd66cabe60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c9d9262cc591e5a663ff1343e1ab5b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f1af12f4eafcde14c51426aec9aa50</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263400</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="H20 Excess Inventory">
  <data key="d0">H20 Excess Inventory</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The H20 excess inventory and purchase obligations resulted in a $4.5 billion charge for NVIDIA in the first quarter of fiscal year 2026, affecting the company's operating income.&lt;SEP&gt;H20 excess inventory refers to the overstock of H20 products that led to a $4.5 billion charge, impacting the gross margin.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fe1fafd9b0c6f09af84ad373757a9b00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777252930</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Purchase Obligations">
  <data key="d0">Purchase Obligations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Purchase obligations are commitments to buy certain products or services in the future, which, when associated with H20 excess inventory, led to a significant charge.&lt;SEP&gt;Purchase Obligations amount to $10.6 billion for goods and services as of October 26, 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Purchase Obligations are non-cancelable commitments the company has made for cloud computing web services, data centers, software, licenses, and services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fe1fafd9b0c6f09af84ad373757a9b00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f659a7f219f7f617d5e8dc482fab75d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a917696681899c306badc63ac69b7d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Third-Party Manufacturers">
  <data key="d0">Third-Party Manufacturers</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Entities responsible for manufacturing products with lead times and constraints that can extend beyond twelve months for some products.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777252931</data>
