<node id="U.S.">
  <data key="d0">U.S.</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The United States (U.S.) is a significant location for the company's business operations, where it is subject to federal and state income taxes. The company holds cash, cash equivalents, and marketable securities in the U.S., which is also a primary location for its business operations. Customers in the U.S. contribute to the company's revenue, making it a crucial market for the organization. The U.S. government implements trade and national security policies, including export controls that can impact the business dealings of the IPLA and Arm China. The country is also subject to complex tax laws and regulations, which are applied to the company's operations. Furthermore, the U.S. is one of the countries that have implemented or are considering implementing changes to tax and accounting laws in line with Pillar Two. The OBBB Act was signed into law in the U.S., where the company conducts business and is subject to local and federal taxes. Overall, the U.S. plays a vital role in the company's financial and operational activities, with a significant portion of its cash and marketable securities held in the country.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a36df99dfa3a16bd8e4d429df7cf42a6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae71f5af8c77cdfb1dcf9e739c3e7b9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bcf7035b2263b22ce2270c9abedd363&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263391</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
