<node id="Gross Profit">
  <data key="d0">Gross Profit</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross profit is a financial metric representing total net revenue less the cost of revenue, which decreased from 75.0% to 71.1% for NVIDIA in fiscal year 2026.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross Profit is the profit after deducting the cost of goods sold from revenue, amounting to $3,435 in 2026 and $3,496 in 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross profit for the year ended December 31, 2024, was $4,491.3 million, a 23.7% increase from the previous year.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross profit is a financial metric that represents the profit a company makes after deducting the costs associated with producing and selling its products, which increased to $5,768.7 million in 2025, up by 28.4% from $4,491.3 million in 2024.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbc7bb48e6d4943b055b0203ce8adb4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263379</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gross Margin">
  <data key="d0">Gross Margin</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross margin is a financial ratio that decreased for NVIDIA from 75.0% to 71.1% in fiscal year 2026 due to a change in business model and a significant charge related to H20 inventory.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross margin is a financial metric representing the company's profitability, which has remained at 64.1%, indicating the company's efficiency in managing costs.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross margin is the percentage of revenue left after deducting the cost of revenue, which remained constant at 64.1% for the years ended December 31, 2025 and 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross margin for the year ended December 31, 2024, was 64.1%, slightly higher than the previous year's 61.9%.&lt;SEP&gt;Gross margin increased from 61.9% in 2023 to 64.1% in 2024, reflecting improved product margins.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fe1fafd9b0c6f09af84ad373757a9b00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c17cee8b5d4c0058ad449ca8d769b9a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69f1af12f4eafcde14c51426aec9aa50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-923b6a774533b6ee182ac5d5b97611cc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bbc7bb48e6d4943b055b0203ce8adb4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263379</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fiscal Year 2026">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal Year 2026</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Fiscal Year 2026 is the most recent fiscal year for which NVIDIA reported financial data, including a decrease in gross margins and revenue growth in specific segments.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 is a period during which the company spent $6.1 billion on capital expenditures.&lt;SEP&gt;Fiscal Year 2026 is the financial year starting on or after July 1, 2025, and ending on or before June 30, 2026, relevant for the implementation of new accounting standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-dd5f5a1a7c540b1c8cafe05b35cfd7fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91ba0c40d4695fe5428e9f1aaee99693&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-528b15deb865d055e3be525ecf5963bc</data>
