<node id="Deferred Tax Assets">
  <data key="d0">Deferred Tax Assets</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3f2ce3a4f3492cdc62d91339c8332500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-528b15deb865d055e3be525ecf5963bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ae71f5af8c77cdfb1dcf9e739c3e7b9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f50e3434e5c216500628bf58a9da4be1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-737963f5a4aa4c7ac5ff75bd66cabe60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bcf7035b2263b22ce2270c9abedd363&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29</data>
  <data key="d2">The Valuation Allowance is used to reduce the Deferred Tax Assets to the amount more likely to be realized.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred tax assets are financial figures representing the tax benefits of future deductions that are recognized in accounting due to temporary differences between book income and taxable income.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Tax Assets are recognized for the estimated future tax effects of temporary differences and for net operating loss and tax credit carryovers.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred tax assets are a financial consideration for AMD, which may be realized or result in tax liabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Deferred Tax Assets are a concept in accounting that represents the tax benefits that can be utilized in the future against taxable income. They require valuation allowances to be assessed for potential impairment.</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263380</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
