  <data key="d2">Senior unsecured notes are a type of debt security that is not backed by any collateral.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Senior unsecured notes with an aggregate principal amount of $6.5 billion outstanding as of October 26, 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Senior Unsecured Notes represent $6.5 billion in aggregate principal amount of notes with varying maturities due beyond 12 months as of October 26, 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Senior Unsecured Notes are debt instruments issued by the company without collateral backing,影响the company's financing activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Senior Unsecured Notes are financial instruments with an aggregate principal amount of $6.5 billion outstanding as of October 26, 2025.</data>
