<node id="Semiconductor Systems">
  <data key="d0">Semiconductor Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">category</data>
  <data key="d2">Semiconductor Systems is one of AMAT's reportable segments, primarily comprising capital equipment used to fabricate semiconductor chips.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Semiconductor Systems is a business segment that reported an operating income of $7,379 million in 2025, showing a 6% increase from 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;Semiconductor Systems is a division of Applied Materials, Inc. that achieved record DRAM revenue.&lt;SEP&gt;Semiconductor Systems is a segment of Applied Materials, Inc. that includes foundry, logic, DRAM, and flash memory, with specific revenue and margin figures.&lt;SEP&gt;Semiconductor Systems is a category within Applied Materials, Inc.'s financial report, detailing the performance of their semiconductor business segment.</data>
