  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Management’s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations (MD&amp;A) is a section of the document that aims to provide an understanding of the company's business and financial results. It is to be read with the Consolidated Financial Statements and other parts of the Form 10-K.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;It is a section in the Annual Report on Form 20-F that discusses the company's financial health and performance.&lt;SEP&gt;"Management’s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations" is a section in the IPO Prospectus discussing critical accounting estimates.</data>
