</node>
<node id="Operating Activities">
  <data key="d0">Operating Activities</data>
  <data key="d1">activity</data>
  <data key="d2">Operating Activities refers to the cash flow from the core business operations of the company, including income and expenses.&lt;SEP&gt;Operating Activities include net income, adjusted for non-cash items, and changes in operating assets and liabilities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263380</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Investing Activities">
  <data key="d0">Investing Activities</data>
  <data key="d1">activity</data>
  <data key="d2">Investing Activities involves cash used for or generated from investments, such as capital expenditures and purchases or sales of investments.&lt;SEP&gt;Investing Activities consist of marketable securities investments, business combinations, and capital expenditures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263380</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Financing Activities">
  <data key="d0">Financing Activities</data>
  <data key="d1">activity</data>
  <data key="d2">Financing Activities encompasses cash flows related to financing the company, including stock repurchases, dividends, and debt repayments.&lt;SEP&gt;Financing Activities involve cash flows related to the company's financing strategies, such as debt or equity financing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263380</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Accounts Receivable">
  <data key="d0">Accounts Receivable</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Accounts Receivable represents the money owed to the company for goods or services provided, which the company has sold on credit.&lt;SEP&gt;Accounts receivable is a financial asset of the Company, affected by the timing of payments from customers.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Accounts Receivable are the amounts due from customers for products and services provided, impacting the company's cash inflows.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88fbdee009d132142f267759b80b8fcd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263380</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Days Sales Outstanding">
  <data key="d0">Days Sales Outstanding</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Days Sales Outstanding is a measure of the average number of days it takes a company to collect payment after a sale has been made.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Capital Expenditures">
  <data key="d0">Capital Expenditures</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Capital Expenditures are funds used by a company to acquire, upgrade, or improve physical assets such as property, industrial buildings, or equipment.&lt;SEP&gt;Capital Expenditures are funds used by a company to acquire, upgrade, and maintain physical assets, amounting to -$646 in 2026 and -$381 in 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Capital Expenditures is a category in the cash flows from investing activities, with expenses of -646 and -381 in two different periods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b33403642cf163673735a8236b77616c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777261185</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Investment Portfolio">
  <data key="d0">Investment Portfolio</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The Investment Portfolio consists of various financial instruments and securities the company holds for potential profit or to manage risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Real Property and Improvements">
  <data key="d0">Real Property and Improvements</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Real Property and Improvements are physical assets that include land and buildings, which the company invests in as part of its capital expenditures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b976a275590777e7877d2d66b5f6379c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777259232</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
