<node id="Acquisitions">
  <data key="d0">Acquisitions</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Acquisitions are the buying of one company by another, which can lead to various risks including failure to realize expected revenues and returns from the acquired businesses.&lt;SEP&gt;Acquisitions are the purchase of other companies or assets, which result in goodwill and intangible assets for the company.&lt;SEP&gt;Acquisitions refer to the completed acquisitions made by Applied Materials, Inc., which result in incremental charges such as amortization of purchased intangible assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Acquisitions refers to the completed acquisitions made by Applied Materials, Inc., which have an impact on their financial statements.&lt;SEP&gt;Acquisitions are business events that can impact AMD's operations and its ability to integrate new businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-158df076948257685462bdd5a2ffcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-531a2d4da0efcbaa075b41456e2d3536&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a29194982b15aafff922b31789e91ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-737963f5a4aa4c7ac5ff75bd66cabe60</data>
