</node>
<node id="Goodwill">
  <data key="d0">Goodwill</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Goodwill represents the excess of the purchase price over the fair value of net assets acquired in a business combination and is periodically reviewed for impairment.&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill is an intangible asset representing the future economic benefits arising from potential synergies of acquired companies, amounting to $3,707 in both 2026 and 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Goodwill is recorded as the excess of consideration transferred over the acquisition-date fair values and is subject to annual impairment assessment.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-625ca1cf50e3b24380c8601c96bdd7a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43a8f055527dad4e87136bbd01caf743&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
