<node id="Income (Loss) from Equity Investments">
  <data key="d0">Income (Loss) from Equity Investments</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Income (loss) from equity investments includes changes in fair value of equity method investments and proportionate share of equity method investee income or loss.&lt;SEP&gt;Income (Loss) from Equity Investments is a category that saw a significant increase in loss by 1085% for the company in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Income (Loss) from Equity Investments represents the company's share of profits or losses from investments in other companies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Other Non-Operating Income (Loss)">
  <data key="d0">Other Non-Operating Income (Loss)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Other non-operating income (loss) includes one-time gains and losses and miscellaneous income and expense items unrelated to core operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Other Non-Operating Income (Loss) is a category that decreased by 9% for the company in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025.&lt;SEP&gt;Other Non-Operating Income (Loss) includes miscellaneous income or expenses not related to the company's main business operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Income Tax Benefit (Expense)">
  <data key="d0">Income Tax Benefit (Expense)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Income tax benefit (expense) is accounted for using the asset and liability method under GAAP, recognizing deferred income taxes for temporary differences.&lt;SEP&gt;Income Tax Benefit (Expense) is a financial concept representing the difference between income tax expenses and benefits recognized by a company under GAAP.&lt;SEP&gt;Income Tax Benefit (Expense) is a category that decreased by 23% for the company in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="U.K.'s &quot;Patent Box&quot;">
  <data key="d0">U.K.'s "Patent Box"</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.K.'s "patent box" is a tax benefit program that the company benefits from, related to patent income.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Arm China">
  <data key="d0">Arm China</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Arm China is a customer and an entity in which the company has an equity method investment, contributing to revenue from related parties.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm China is an organization with which an agreement for software engineering-related services was terminated in December 2023.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm China is a related party that sublicenses Arm's processor technology and generates a significant portion of Arm's total revenue.&lt;SEP&gt;Arm China is an organization that provides financial information to the IPLA and is involved in transactions that may be affected by political actions and export control regulations.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca207bb382651453029b45cb72e9feff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5068f4b1da4cd023617e872a463eeb62</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Consolidated Income Statements">
  <data key="d0">Consolidated Income Statements</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Consolidated Income Statements is a financial report that includes various expenses and income details.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consolidated Income Statements are financial reports that include the company's total revenue, costs, and profits, presented as a percentage of total revenue.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consolidated Income Statements is the financial report where the impact of revisions of original estimates is recognized.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Finance Leases">
  <data key="d0">Finance Leases</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Finance leases are a type of financial agreement that generates interest expense for the company.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8b7994a7b9c5c9289cc48f3afe48287c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OECD">
  <data key="d0">OECD</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The OECD is an international organization that reached an agreement to implement a minimum 15% tax rate on certain multinational enterprises, known as Pillar Two.&lt;SEP&gt;The OECD is an international organization that reached an agreement for implementing a minimum tax rate on multinational enterprises, known as Pillar Two.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pillar Two">
  <data key="d0">Pillar Two</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pillar Two refers to a global tax framework agreed upon by the OECD to implement a minimum 15% tax rate on certain multinational enterprises.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="U.K.">
  <data key="d0">U.K.</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The U.K. is a significant jurisdiction for the company's business operations and taxes, offering a "patent box" regime for certain profits.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.K. is a location where legislation was enacted to implement the OECD's Pillar Two framework.&lt;SEP&gt;The U.K. is a country that enacted legislation to implement the OECD's Pillar Two framework, with parts of it going into effect on January 1, 2024.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Union">
  <data key="d0">European Union</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Union is a political and economic union of countries, many of which have implemented or are considering changes to tax and accounting laws in line with Pillar Two.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Form 20-F">
  <data key="d0">Form 20-F</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Form 20-F is an annual report filed by the Company, which includes a discussion and analysis of financial condition and results of operations.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Form 20-F is the annual report filed by the company with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, detailing its financial performance and other significant information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a917696681899c306badc63ac69b7d7</data>
