<node id="Property and Equipment">
  <data key="d0">Property and Equipment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Property and equipment are assets of the Company, which have seen an increase in purchases.&gt;&lt;SEP&gt;Property and Equipment are tangible assets that are used in the normal course of business and are expected to be used for more than one accounting period.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42aa9c7f7d4ca12621cf2af559e1aa29</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777263380</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Short-Term Investments">
  <data key="d0">Short-Term Investments</data>
  <data key="d1">financialasset</data>
  <data key="d2">Short-term investments are a financial asset of the Company, used to finance operations.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-13f18e1b9ab8662fc4105918eb9e67e8</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IPLA">
  <data key="d0">IPLA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The IPLA is an agreement that grants Arm China the right to sublicense Arm's processor technology and dictates the financial relationship between Arm and Arm China.&lt;SEP&gt;The IPLA is an organization that has financial dealings with Arm China, relying on their provided financial information for determining payments due.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5068f4b1da4cd023617e872a463eeb62</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PRC">
  <data key="d0">PRC</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The PRC is a country whose government's policies, along with those of the U.S., can influence the business environment and transactions involving the IPLA and Arm China.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bureau of Industry and Security">
  <data key="d0">Bureau of Industry and Security</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">&gt;The Bureau of Industry and Security, part of the U.S. Department of Commerce, is responsible for extending the reach of U.S. export controls on the semiconductor industry.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Implementation of Additional Due Diligence Measures for Advanced Computing Integrated Circuits">
  <data key="d0">Implementation of Additional Due Diligence Measures for Advanced Computing Integrated Circuits</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Implementation of Additional Due Diligence Measures for Advanced Computing Integrated Circuits is an interim final rule published by BIS with a compliance date of January 31, 2025, affecting PRC entities and the semiconductor industry.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Framework for Artificial Intelligence Diffusion">
  <data key="d0">Framework for Artificial Intelligence Diffusion</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Framework for Artificial Intelligence Diffusion, also known as the AI Diffusion Rule, is an interim final rule introduced to impose worldwide export license requirements on advanced computing products.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GAAFET">
  <data key="d0">GAAFET</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">GAAFET, or Gate all-around Field-Effect Transistor, is a technology for which new restrictions on exporting, re-exporting, or transferring to the PRC and other countries were established.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="HBM">
  <data key="d0">HBM</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">HBM, or High Bandwidth Memory, is a technology that faces new restrictions on being exported, re-exported, or transferred to the PRC and other countries.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RTL-based CSSs">
  <data key="d0">RTL-based CSSs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">RTL-based CSSs, or Chip Design Software Suites, are part of the advanced products and technologies the IPLA is interested in developing.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GDSII-based CSSs">
  <data key="d0">GDSII-based CSSs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">GDSII-based CSSs, or Chip Design Software Suites, are part of the advanced products and technologies the IPLA is interested in developing.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chiplets">
  <data key="d0">Chiplets</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Chiplets are part of the advanced products and technologies the IPLA is interested in developing.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="End Chip Solutions">
  <data key="d0">End Chip Solutions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">End Chip Solutions are part of the advanced products and technologies the IPLA is interested in developing.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Outsourced Semiconductor Assembly and Test">
  <data key="d0">Outsourced Semiconductor Assembly and Test</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Outsourced Semiconductor Assembly and Test, referred to as OSAT, are vendors designated to mitigate the risk of diversion as per the new rules by BIS.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="BIS Entity List">
  <data key="d0">BIS Entity List</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The BIS Entity List is a list maintained by the Bureau of Industry and Security that includes new entities added to it, affecting export controls.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d028a96cd827e54a97bfc99b9a77942a</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Share-based Compensation">
  <data key="d0">Share-based Compensation</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Share-based Compensation refers to the accounting practice of expensing awards over the service periods, typically equivalent to the vesting term, and is only recorded for awards expected to vest.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RSUs">
  <data key="d0">RSUs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">RSUs are awards with a fair value based on the grant date fair value for share-based awards, calculated using the closing price of the Company’s ADSs on Nasdaq.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PSUs">
  <data key="d0">PSUs</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">PSUs are awards granted with relative total shareholder return as the performance measure under the Omnibus Incentive Plan, measured over a three-year period against the S&amp;P 500 IT Sector Index.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Relative TSR">
  <data key="d0">Relative TSR</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Relative TSR is the performance measure used for PSUs, determining the vesting potential between 0% and 200% of the original award amount.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Monte Carlo simulation model">
  <data key="d0">Monte Carlo simulation model</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Monte Carlo simulation model is used to determine the grant date fair value of the market conditions component of awards with Relative TSR-based performance measures.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Reporting Unit">
  <data key="d0">Reporting Unit</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Reporting Unit is the entity against which the annual impairment assessment of goodwill is performed.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Income Method">
  <data key="d0">Income Method</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Income Method is one of the approaches used to estimate a reporting unit’s fair value in the goodwill impairment test.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Market Method">
  <data key="d0">Market Method</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Market Method is another approach used to estimate a reporting unit’s fair value in the goodwill impairment test.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deferred Taxes">
  <data key="d0">Deferred Taxes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Deferred Taxes are accounted for using the asset and liability method under GAAP, based on temporary differences between financial reporting and tax bases.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="United Kingdom">
  <data key="d0">United Kingdom</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The United Kingdom is one of the jurisdictions where the Company is subject to income taxes.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="S&amp;P 500 IT Sector Index">
  <data key="d0">S&amp;P 500 IT Sector Index</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The S&amp;P 500 IT Sector Index is a benchmark used for measuring the performance of PSUs with Relative TSR as the performance measure.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Nasdaq">
  <data key="d0">Nasdaq</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Nasdaq is the stock market where the Company’s ADSs are traded, and its closing price is used to determine the fair value of RSUs.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1fc03c6340e9f91435287101b7ba57e5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Omnibus Incentive Plan">
  <data key="d0">Omnibus Incentive Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Omnibus Incentive Plan is the plan under which the Company grants PSUs with Relative TSR as the performance measure.&gt;</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8e2d85f7a44ae4d46a5296c95183929c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fiscal Year Ended March 31, 2025">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal Year Ended March 31, 2025</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Fiscal Year Ended March 31, 2025 is a specific period for which the company's financial performance is being evaluated and compared to previous years.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fiscal Year Ended March 31, 2024">
  <data key="d0">Fiscal Year Ended March 31, 2024</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Fiscal Year Ended March 31, 2024 is a comparative period for analyzing the company's financial performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262952</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Revenue from External Customers">
  <data key="d0">Revenue from External Customers</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Revenue from External Customers represents the income generated from customers outside the company, constituting a significant portion of total revenue.&lt;SEP&gt;Revenue from external customers is a primary source of income for the company, influenced by the same factors as license and other revenue and royalty revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Revenue from Related Parties">
  <data key="d0">Revenue from Related Parties</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Revenue from Related Parties indicates income generated from transactions within related parties, contributing to the company's total revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca207bb382651453029b45cb72e9feff</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Royalty Revenue">
  <data key="d0">Royalty Revenue</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Royalty Revenue is a type of income derived from licensing agreements and is a component of the company's total revenue.&lt;SEP&gt;Royalty revenue is a part of the company's income, influenced by the same factors as license and other revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="License and Other Revenue">
  <data key="d0">License and Other Revenue</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">License and Other Revenue includes revenue from licensing, software development tools, design services, training, support, and other fees not constituting royalty revenue.&lt;SEP&gt;License and Other Revenue includes income from new licensing agreements and renewals, contributing to the company's total revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fe18d577f076ce03948540ed8563a5c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="U.S. Federal and State Income Taxes">
  <data key="d0">U.S. Federal and State Income Taxes</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">U.S. Federal and State Income Taxes are taxes that the company must pay to federal and state governments in the U.S., based on its income.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Patent Box Regime">
  <data key="d0">Patent Box Regime</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Patent Box Regime is a tax policy in the U.K. that allows certain profits from patented products to be taxed at a reduced rate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Net Income (Loss)">
  <data key="d0">Net Income (Loss)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Net Income (Loss) represents the company's profit or loss after all revenues, costs, expenses, and taxes have been accounted for.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operating Income (Loss)">
  <data key="d0">Operating Income (Loss)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Operating Income (Loss) is the company's profit or loss from its normal business operations, excluding income from investments and interest.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cost of Sales">
  <data key="d0">Cost of Sales</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cost of sales, comprised primarily of the costs of providing technical support, training, and other services to customers.&lt;SEP&gt;Cost of Sales represents the direct costs associated with producing the goods or services sold by the company.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca207bb382651453029b45cb72e9feff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gross Profit (Loss)">
  <data key="d0">Gross Profit (Loss)</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Gross Profit (Loss) is the company's profit or loss after deducting the cost of goods sold from revenue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Selling, General and Administrative">
  <data key="d0">Selling, General and Administrative</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Selling, General and Administrative expenses cover the costs of marketing, management, and general office overhead.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Income (Loss) Before Income Taxes">
  <data key="d0">Income (Loss) Before Income Taxes</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Income (Loss) Before Income Taxes is the company's profit or loss before considering the impact of income taxes.&lt;SEP&gt;Income (loss) before income taxes is a financial metric that increased by 240% for the company in the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1bd342ebc79b6c8d6a4c0db7019159b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b11abf58ed4d75a128d8d943d08096f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Net Cash Provided by (Used for) Financing Activities">
  <data key="d0">Net Cash Provided by (Used for) Financing Activities</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">This event refers to the financial activities that resulted in a net cash flow for the fiscal year ended March 31, 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a917696681899c306badc63ac69b7d7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Contractual Obligations and Commitments">
  <data key="d0">Contractual Obligations and Commitments</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">These are the binding agreements that the company has, which include lease payments and purchase obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a917696681899c306badc63ac69b7d7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1777262953</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
