<node id="Cost of Revenue">
  <data key="d0">Cost of Revenue</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Cost of revenue includes the expenses associated with manufacturing products and providing services, which increased by $725.2 million, or 28.9%, for the year ended December 31, 2025 compared to 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;Total cost of revenue for the year ended December 31, 2024, was $2,511.8 million, a 12.6% increase from the previous year.&lt;SEP&gt;Cost of revenue is a financial metric that represents the total expenses directly associated with the production of the company's products/services, which increased to $3,237.0 million in 2025, up by 28.9% from $2,511.8 million in 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;The cost of revenue increased by $282.0 million, driven by increased product and service revenues.</data>
